OL,3,CGPs vote in favour of 'unprecedented'
OL,4,Ccollective action over funding dispute
OL,6,FNorthern Ireland General Practitioners
OL,7,FCommittee (NIGPC) chairwoman Dr
OL,8,FFrances O'Hagan said: "The decision to
OL,9,Ftake collective action has not been
OL,10,Fmade lightly; it is a last resort to
OL,11,Fdraw attention to the critical needs
OL,12,Fof the general practice and to
OL,13,Fadvocate for immediate funding and
OL,14,Fsustainable solutions.
OL,16,F"We have taken comprehensive legal
OL,17,Fadvice and are making every effort to
OL,18,Fensure that patient care remains as
OL,19,Funaffected as possible during
OL,20,Fcollective action.
OL,26,@pD@WOUxD@AOU
