OL,3,CGPs vote in favour of 'unprecedented'
OL,4,Ccollective action over funding dispute
OL,6,F"We need to reopen the negotiation for
OL,7,Fthis year, and the minister allocate
OL,8,Fadditional resources immediately to
OL,9,Fstabilise general practice and to
OL,10,Fengage in constructive discussions for
OL,11,Fsustainable, long-term improvements.
OL,13,F"Only when he has done that can we
OL,14,Fbegin to talk about next year and how
OL,15,FGPs can work with the rest of the
OL,16,Fsystem to move more care into the
OL,17,Fcommunity.
OL,19,F"We need immediate action to stabilise
OL,20,Fservices before we can plan for long
OL,21,Fterm changes and improvements."
